title: UST is LIT
body:
One of the most awaited events of a Thomasian is the opening of the Paskuhan Festivities for the year! It is the start of a month-long celebration of Christmas the Thomasian way.

I decided to VLOG. (Yehey! First VLOG ever! What could possibly go wrong?) I know I’m not the best vlogger [yet] but I’ll get a hang of it. You can check out the VLOG here:

https://youtu.be/6_X4cUUTAzY

Going back, all classes in the university were suspended at exactly 4:00 PM so that all the students and faculty from different colleges could attend the University Mass, AGAPE and the Lighting of the Campus.

This year’s Paskuhan is inspired by the Game of Thrones. We are to celebrate the birth of Jesus Christ, the “King of Kings” on a Wednesday, the 20th of December. According to some administrators, this Paskuhan 2017 will be full of surprises!

The University Mass took place at the UST Plaza Mayor at exactly 4:30 PM. It was presided by UST Rector, Very Rev. Fr. Herminio V. Dagohoy, O.P., concelebrated with Dominican priests. He gave a remarkable homily for Thomasians about following Jesus and about hope. Hope for us students, in all the requirements that we have to do. Hope for us who experience and face many problems in life and that we should always remember to look up to God. We should exert our efforts and it is up to God to give us what we deserve.

After the mass was the AGAPE. Around the university were several stations of different restaurants where in each college were asked to line up. You just need your Student ID and there you go, you have free dinner! Too bad the supplies didn’t last for everyone.

The lighting of the campus started at the Plaza Mayor at around 6 PM. It came with a short fireworks display and a second later, the whole campus was sparkling with colorful Christmas lights. Most of the Christmas lights were hung on all of the trees, some were attached to sticks and planted on the ground, shining doves (made up of garlands) that showed the essence of Christmas, and a big dragon in front of the Main Building to show the theme and many more Christmas decorations.
